<h1>From James Gildart</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Leverpool [England] Octor 31st 1768</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>I received your kind favor of the 25th June <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">mutilated</span> extreamly sorry to hear the 25 Sacks of Salt Sent you <img class="char" src="images/char-per-trans.png" alt="[per]"/> the Oak McDaniel came in such bad order and so unseason[a]bly<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> that Ship was intendd for Geo. Town to take in a Cargoe of Grain my Agt had bought of one Mr Ballandine who disapointed him that on the Ship Arrivall at St Marys after a passage of 17 weekes, he the Agent ordered her to Baltimore,<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> &amp; the Stupid Ignorant Master took the Salt up with him instead of forwarding that it
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-08-02-pb-0139">[139]</span>
was tumbled about for 5 months ere it Came to your hands &amp; I put to the Lord knowns what Charge thereon As to the Sacking it was most Certain as you say very bad but give me leave to Assure you quite New from the Makers when it went from hence, I have more pleasure in getting Sacking than In All the Goods I buy &amp; I never bought <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">illegible</span> In my Life wth a <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">mutilated</span> ready money for it. I have now been 4 months in C<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">mutilated</span>ing sufficient for this Ship. &amp; after All its errant Track liker Crocus than Sacking; I blame my Self for not markg the Sacks According to your order &amp; for wc. I begg your Pardon, herewith you have the Accot Sales of young Mr Custises four hhd Tobo recd <img class="char" src="images/char-per-trans.png" alt="[per]"/> the JnoSon Ntt Proceeds 40.12.2 with my Acct Currt as you desire<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0003" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> wch hope will be found right &amp; that you will be pleased to Note it Accordg. Tobo are now in demand Selling from 2 to 3 that I hope the small Stocke we have on hand will very soon be run off &amp; the early New Tobo come to a good Markett this has Induced me Sending the Totness for Rappk directly to take in what early Tobos my Friends incline to ship &amp; for dispatch fill up wth wheat wch is Now from 6/ to 6/4 70 Lb. our Parliamt which meet In a few days I hope will prolong the time for its Importatn duty free from America or I am Sure our Poor will be half Starved. I have seen a sample of your last Crop which was most Curious Grain a fine Colour &amp; will feed. hope that fine Crop will enrich your farmers bravely are they are Certain of a demand from Italy &amp;c. our Rope makers give no encouragt for your hemp Complaining of its being so Ill dressed &amp; such a Vast Loss in the Manufacture.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0004" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0004-ptr">4</a></p>
<p>I Shall <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">mutilated</span> Sen<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">mutilated</span> small Ship for york River tobo &amp; hope for a Continuance Friendship &amp; assistance towd her loading &amp; am with much respt Sir Yr Most Ob. Set</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Jame. Gildart</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0108-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Virginia Historical Society, Richmond ]">ViHi</span>: Custis Papers.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Daniel McDaniel was captain of the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Oak.</span> Gildarts invoice for the salt is dated 13 July 1767. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0004" class="document">Gildart to GW, 16 July 1767</a>. Gildarts letter and the salt did not arrive until April 1768.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>The port of Georgetown, Md., on the Potomac River, is now a part of Washington, D.C. John Ballendine, whose financial difficulties had forced him to turn over his Occoquan mills and iron manufactory to John Semple, had established by about 1765 another large commercial complex at the Little Falls of the Potomac, near Georgetown, which included merchant mills and a
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-08-02-pb-0140">[140]</span>
 bakery. See <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Donald Jackson and Dorothy Twohig, eds. &lt;i&gt;The Diaries of George Washington&lt;/i&gt;. 6 vols. Charlottesville, Va., 197679. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Diaries</span></span>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-01-02-02-0005-0003#GEWN-01-02-02-pb-0213" class="document">2:213</a>. St. Marys in Maryland is on the point where the Potomac flows into the Chesapeake Bay.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Capt. John Mulloy of the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Johnson</span> transported four hogsheads of John Parke Custiss tobacco to Gildart in 1766. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-07-02-0303" class="document">GW to Gildart, 21 July 1766</a>. The account current has not been found.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0108-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p><a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-07-02-0303" class="document">GW mentions in his letter to Gildart of 21 July 1766</a> having sent a sample of his hemp. He also must have sent a small amount of wheat in 1767. There is no record of his hereafter sending either hemp or wheat to Gildart for sale.</p>

</div>
</div>
